UMUAHIA – The Chancellor of Gregory University Uturu (GUU) and gubernatorial candidate of the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA), Prof Grego­ry Ibe, has expressed joy at the release of the Prelate of Meth­odist Church, Rt Rev Samuel Kalu Uche, and two others by kidnappers. The don, in a statement made available to newsmen in Umuahia, stated that the abduc­tion of the head of the Method­ist Church in Nigeria devastat­ed him, stressing that the news cut short of the celebration of his victory as APGA’s governor­ship candidate.He said, “When the news broke on Sunday of the kidnap of the Prelate, who happens to be my revered se­nior at the Ihube High School, it became a killjoy development that doused celebrations of my victory at the just concluded gu­ber primary election of APGA. “Therefore, my joy knows no bounds hearing of his release in good health”. -Advertisement- According to Ibe, the issue of insecurity especially around the Isuikwuato and Umunneo­chi axis has become a nagging problem that must be urgently addressed to curb the ever-in­creasing frequency of kidnap­ping. The proprietor of the Grego­ry University tasked the Feder­al and Abia State governments as well as governments in the Southeast geopolitical zone to formally incorporate local vig­ilante groups in their security infrastructure.